---
source: src/sphinxdocrs/tests/autogen.rs
expression: cmd.render_help().to_string()
---
Generate ReStructuredText using autosummary directives.

sphinx-autogen is a frontend to sphinx.ext.autosummary.generate. It generates the reStructuredText files from the autosummary directives contained in the given input files.

Usage: sphinx-autogen [OPTIONS] <SOURCE_FILE>...

Arguments:
  <SOURCE_FILE>...  source files to generate rST files for

Options:
  -o, --output-dir <OUTPUT_DIR>  directory to place all output in
  -s, --suffix <SUFFIX>          default suffix for files (default: rst) [default: rst]
  -t, --templates <TEMPLATES>    custom template directory (default: None)
  -i, --imported-members         document imported members (default: false)
  -a, --respect-module-all       document exactly the members in module __all__ attribute. (default: false)
      --remove-old               Remove existing files in the output directory that were not generated
      --use-python-impl          delegate to the upstream Python sphinx-autogen
  -h, --help                     Print help
